{
  "name": "Protein Cookie Dough Bars",
  "description": "Frosted no-bake cookie-dough bars: a Greek-yogurt + peanut-butter + oat-flour cookie-dough base pressed in a loaf pan, topped with a blended cottage-cheese/cream-cheese protein frosting (tinted with spirulina, flavored with cake-batter extract) and a crushed sandwich cookie. Same frosted-bar format as the Lemon and Peppermint bars; the frosting is the cottage/cream-cheese protein style of the Protein Cream-Cheese Frosting sub-recipe. Maple/honey kept as written (no-bake binder). Microwave 6-7 s straight from the freezer to serve.",
  "tags": [
    "protein",
    "cookie-dough",
    "frosted",
    "no-bake",
    "bars",
    "made"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 7,
    "unit": "bars"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "b1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "base",
        "instructionText": "Mix the Greek yogurt, peanut butter, softened butter, honey, protein, oat flour, vanilla, and salt until thick; fold in the chocolate chips. Press into a parchment-lined loaf pan."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "f1",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "frosting",
        "instructionText": "Blend the cottage cheese, cream cheese, maple syrup, protein, spirulina, vanilla, and cake-batter extract until very smooth. Spread over the base."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "t1",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "topping",
        "instructionText": "Scatter the broken-up sandwich cookie over the top. Freeze 30-60 min, thaw 10 min, then slice into 7 bars. Microwave 6-7 s from frozen to serve."
      }
    ],
